Vim Configuration
George Lesica <george@lesica.com>

This is my Vim configuration. It uses Pathogen to manage plugins and includes a
handy script to set up all the necessary symlinks without totally clobbering
the existing configuration files.

A list of plugins I am using, including links, can be found at 
http://lesica.com/vim-plugins.html

Some notes on setup and using Pathogen:

To clone submodules (plugin repos):

    git submodule init
    git submodule update

To add an additional plugin repo:

    git submodule add <remote> vim/bundle/<name>
    git commit -m 'Added plugin <name>'

To use Vimballs:

    :e name.vba
    :!mkdir ~/.vim/bundle/name
    :UseVimball ~/.vim/bundle/name
